content.description: This climb is loaded with enjoyable moves and nice jugs the whole way. Just when you think it's over the crux will pop up with a nice deadpoint. This line is a great warm-up for the area!
content.location: This is the first bolted line to the left of Particle Man, and is about 25 feet to the right of Vine Street

content.description:
Follow inside corner, hand and finger sized...astro boy is the face on the left of the corner...for newbies this is often the second route done at the bluff 

  left side of dihedral is solid, right side shattered
content.protection:
toprope...avoid the manky birch. Lead if you want to, but pro may be suspect and i would give it an R rating 

  Bring long slings 50'+

content.description:
up face between Flake Route and Dirty overhang is a finger crack that starts 25' off the ground.... 

  Climb to thru loose lower band to an ok band, then on to rough finger crack.
content.location: Just left of rounded arete that marks end of Astro dog face is 20' wide face that is ends with the Dirty Overhang route that has several distinct lines all checking in about 5.7-.8

content.description: climb dirty ledges to 5' overhang 15' up...pull overhang to hand crack above...big big overhang for the grade...back in the day there was a pommel that one had to straddle when pulling overhang, adding a certain pucker factor to the move, even on TR...thankfully this knob is gone now

Generally easy climbing with one hard move at the second bolt, blocky with big holds beyond the crux. Equipped with chains and hooks. From the anchor, you can access and top rope the hand crack to the climber's right.
New route to the right of Particle Man. Need some cleaning but climbs well with big holds and ledges. Chain anchor with fixed hooks.
content.protection: 6 glue in bolts plus a fixed anchor

content.description: Climb up blasting scar between Double Overhang and Particle Man. Very dirty, very loose (fist to head sized). Don't even bother.
Drop rope down from V-notch on the large table-sized block on top. Climb up plumb line. Chicken out right to The S--- Stain.

content.location: From the main parking lot walk south to the look out. Continue on the path that takes you down the bluff to George's Point and half way down the bluff the boulder will be on the right.

content.description: Climb route that moves up over large flake to the left of Astro Boy.  Can be a bit dirty and crumbly, but a good route for starting climbers.  It was my very first climb many years ago.
Climb up center of wall to 2' overhang, move right and climb up diagonal undercling crack through a water stain. 5.9+ if you pull the overhang.
Start just to the left of George's warm up, and climb up and to the left. Stay low while moving left then move up at the highest point on the boulderÂ
content.location: Just to the left of George's warm up. On the way down to George's Point

content.description: Face climb to the left of the inside corner crack.
content.protection: Glue-in bolts and chain anchors with carabiners to lower.

content.description: Route climbs right of the Vine Street Dihedral with 7 bolts and a chain anchor. The crux has 2 options being straight up the corner or traverse right onto Astro boy for a few face moves. We protected with good movement

Routes here are primarily beginner level, and are best done as TR problems. This crag unfortunately is another popular place to go "office space" on printer, computers etc. So watch out for lots of broken glass, and busted appliances. Come here only if you are desperate for something  new.  

  Climbing is not illegal at George's Point Park, but is prohibited on the big and obvious faces of Grandad's Bluff, closest to the overlook which is a City Park. There is not any City policy or ordinance about climbing, in order to further reduce any liability for the City, but climbing is allowed in the bluffs.
